Description: DefineMe is has a clear mission: to empower self-worth and confidence through scent, and use sustainable and good for you ingredients.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: DefineMe is a visionary fragrance company founded by Jennifer McKay Newton with a clear mission: to empower self-worth and confidence through scent. The journey began when Jennifer witnessed her daughter's struggles and recognized similar challenges within herself and others. This inspired her to create a brand that would make a positive difference in people's lives. What sets us apart at DefineMe is our unwavering commitment to conscious beauty practices. We firmly believe in using only natural, organic, and toxic-free ingredients in our fragrances and products, aligning with the values of customers who prioritize sustainability and ethical choices. We want our customers to feel good about the products they use and the impact they have on themselves and the environment. Ethics and compassion are at the core of our brand. We are proud to be cruelty-free and vegan, ensuring that no animals are harmed in the production of our fragrances, home, and bath and body products. Additionally, we take sustainability seriously by incorporating sustainable packaging materials to minimize our environmental footprint. By embracing local manufacturing in California, we not only support our community but also reduce transportation-related carbon emissions. But our dedication doesn't stop there. We are driven by a strong commitment to social impact. Since 2016, we have proudly supported She's The First, a remarkable nonprofit organization dedicated to combating gender inequality by providing assistance to girls in underprivileged areas, enabling them to become the first in their families to graduate from high school. We wholeheartedly believe in the incredible work led by Tammy Tibbets and her team, and as part of our commitment, we pledge a portion of our annual profits to She's The First. At DefineMe, we are more than just a fragrance company. We are a movement that empowers individuals, embraces conscious beauty practices, utilizes sustainable packaging, and makes a positive impact on society. By choosing DefineMe, you not only discover captivating scents but also support a brand that values self-worth, the environment, and the education of young women around the world. Join us on this inspiring journey.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Community and Lifestyle, Consumer Goods

Description: Sightbox is a vision service for contact lens wearers.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Sightbox is a vision service for people who wear contact lenses. Each membership includes an eye exam, contact lens fitting, an annual supply of contacts, and a payment plan to spread out the customer's cost over the course of a year. The Sightbox team works from the Pittock Block in downtown Portland, Oregon. Formerly a power generator station for the city and print room for The Oregonian newspaper, it is now home to many of the area's leading tech companies.  Our five distribution centers are located across the US. Sightbox is designed for people who need new contacts and don’t have a current prescription. We spread out the high upfront cost of vision care into simple monthly payments. When a new member joins Sightbox our first priority is to refer them to a local optometrist for a comprehensive exam. We schedule the appointment, pay the doctor, and provide the patient with an annual supply of contacts. Sightbox supports all major manufacturer disposable lenses including toric, multifocal, and color contact within our standard vision memberships.  Sightbox is available in all 50 US states. An annual membership is $39 per month and includes your eye exam, contact lens fitting, and an annual supply of 2-Week or Monthly contacts. We also offer an upgrade option, with flexible pricing, for members who wish to wear 1-Day contacts.

Description: Paratus Diagnostics is developing a portfolio of point-of-care diagnostic devices that will make healthcare.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Paratus Diagnostics, LLC is an early stage company founded in 2012 by Dr. John C. Carrano that focuses on point-of-care diagnostic solutions. The company is headquartered at a new and state-of-the-art technology incubator called the STAR Park (www.txstate.edu/starpark). Following a “hub-and-spoke” model we have built a central holding company from which we will incubate several different yet complimentary subsidiaries each with its own market application and commensurate product and technology focus. The business structure is very much consistent with the original premise of Paratus Diagnostics that a common denominator missing from all diagnostic and biological detection solutions is the lack of a simplified sample preparation solution. The genesis of our company was built on the notion that a universal module could be constructed that would address this gap in the in-vitro diagnostics landscape and enable many different diagnostic applications and assay formats without the need for trained laboratory technicians and equipment while maintaining a common core design and manufacturing structure. We have trademarked this common core as the Paratus SDS®, a low-cost consumable cartridge which can be tailored for a variety of assay formats and biological samples to meet numerous diagnostic needs. While the impetus for the Paratus SDS® was the need for a simplified and highly automated sample preparation solution, each cartridge is capable of performing a completely self-contained assay, enabling a true sample-to-answer solution.

Description: Online Marketplace for Sustainable Food / Whole Foods for the 99%
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Wholeshare is an online marketplace for sustainable and organic food.  Our investors in the food space call us "Whole Foods for the 99%".  Only one quarter of the US lives in an area that can support a store like Whole Foods because of the volumes needed to run a natural foods supermarket with 25K products.  However, demand for sustainable products is widespread (>$100B/yr) and rapidly growing.  Wholeshare enables consumers in every US geography to buy sustainable food at wholesale prices through shopping as a group.  Wholeshare members shop for their groceries online and receive products directly from natural food distributors and local food hubs.  By tapping into existing wholesale networks, our members are able to save money and get access to foods that they might not have in their communities. Wholeshare's group-based model solves the last mile problems that have plagued food distribution.  We recently started offering 25K products nationally through a partnership with UNFI, the largest natural food distributor in the US.  Our sales from that offering has been increasing 65% month-over-month since August, and our total sales currently average about $170K per month.  We are proud to have been funded by venture investors such as Andreessen Horowitz, SV Angel, 500 Startups, and BoxGroup, as well as several impact investors with deep expertise in the food space.

Description: StarMobile is a codeless, cloud-based platform that delivers enterprise mobility.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: StarMobile is a codeless, cloud-based enterprise mobility platform that allows companies to dynamically transform any application (on-premise or cloud-based applications, or custom systems based on the web, .NET, Win32, Java, Flash, or "green screen") for use on any endpoint with native user experience and native device integration, faster, simpler and at a lower cost than any solution on the planet. Founded in 2012, StarMobile has conceived in the Georgia Tech Networking and Mobile Computing (GNAN) Research Laboratory, under grants from the Georgia Research Alliance and the National Science Foundation. StarMobile employs a revolutionary remote computing protocol called “MORPH” (five patents pending) that was commercialized at VentureLab, the #2 University Business Incubator in the world, under grants from the Georgia Research Alliance and the National Science Foundation. MORPH intelligently derives the mobile app directly from the original application, then applies a series of transformations in real-time to render a native mobile experience to the end-user. StarMobile requires no changes to existing applications, no coding, no exotic skills, no re-building, simple configuration, and low maintenance, with infinite scalability, end-to-end security, and detailed analytics, for any application, any use case, and any endpoint, with native user experience and native device integration. StarMobile is based in Atlanta, Georgia, and its leadership team has 125+ years of experience in enterprise software, mobile computing, and networking at recognized companies, as well as successful startups.

Traditional use of curcumin has been restricted to topical skin and gastrointestinal conditions because of negligible absorption when given orally. To extend its clinical use Signpath is developing three different intravenous nanoparticle-sized formulations; liposomal, polymeric, and PLGA. Description: ​Arrevus is a Research Triangle Park-based biotech company.
Headquarters Regions: Research Triangle, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Although there is a clear increase in bacteria “resistant” to standard therapies in a “test tube”, the real importance of resistance is when it becomes a clinical problem because of decreased effectiveness to treat serious life-threatening disease in patients by affecting clinical outcomes, such as mortality, decreased function and decreased quality of life for patients.  For some diseases that are self-resolving and for which antibiotics aren’t required (e.g., sinusitis, bronchitis, otitis media, skin abscesses), identification of antibiotic resistance remains a test tube phenomenon with little impact on patient outcomes.  More concerning illnesses, such as serious disease due to methicillin-resistant S. aureus (MRSA), resistance may indeed result in decreased effectiveness for some older drugs but many therapies still remain and many new therapies currently exist to treat MRSA.  Arrevus is focusing its drug development efforts on those diseases for which antibiotic resistance has important clinical implications and for which few therapies exist.  These efforts are dedicated to the development of Designer Proline-rich Antimicrobial Peptide Chaperone Protein Inhibitors (“DPCs”)
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering
Top 5 Investors: U.S. Department of Defense, North Carolina Biotechnology Center

Description: Theranostics Health is a proteomics-based diagnostics company that provides research services for drug development companies.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Theranostics Health is a proteomics-based diagnostics company that provides research services to drug development companies and is developing diagnostic tests to enable personalized cancer therapies tailored to each patient’s tumor. Its technologies utilize Laser Capture Microdissection (LCM) and Reverse-phase Protein MicroArrays (RPMA) assays to accurately measure drug targets and their signaling pathways within tumor cells. Its technologies are of particular use for companies developing Molecular Targeted Therapies and allow insights into the phospho-activation status of drug targets, their downstream pathways and potential survival mechanisms or pathways within targeted cell populations and are utilized in a translational research manner from preclinical SAR-type studies through to Phase II clinical trials.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering
